VCDM

Includes drafts of:
- CDMI server 
- CMDI clients (.Net, Java, curl, python)
- buildbot conf
- docs
- sample server credentials (!!! never use them in production !!!)

Each should get its own git repo.


=== SETUP ===

1) Get the contents of the repository.
	- git clone git://github.com/livenson/vcdm.git
	- wget -O vcdm.zip --no-check-certificate https://github.com/livenson/vcdm/zipball/master && unzip vcdm.zip
	- browse to https://github.com/livenson/vcdm, click on Downloads

2) For a completely local installation:
	- install required Python packages:
		- Zope.Interface: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/zope.interface
		- Twisted: http://twistedmatrix.com
		- Boto: http://code.google.com/p/boto/
		- CouchDB-Python: http://code.google.com/p/couchdb-python/
		- py-amqplib: http://barryp.org/software/py-amqplib/
	- install RabbitMQ: http://www.rabbitmq.com/
	- install CouchDB: http://couchdb.apache.org/

If you are using Ubuntu: 
	- apt-get install python-zope.interface python-twisted python-boto python-couchdb python-amqplib rabbitmq-server couchdb


	
3) Copy vcdm.conf.template to vcdm.conf.

4) Run start-server.sh/start-server.bat.
	- by default, ports 8080-8083 will be accessible.



 
